17/08/21, 13:22 - +91 79038 55076: *Club:* Ayuda NGO
*Event Name:* Life through your lens 2.0
*Date:* 19 August

*Event Description:*
Click, Capture and Repeat!
Photography- when the words become unclear and a story we fail to put into words. Its a work of passion and dedication, its the photographer and not the camera which makes it so desirable.
The power of lens not only captures humans but expresses deep emotions. It is an austere and blazing poetry of the real. When you photograph people in colour you capture the appearance but when you do it in B&W you resonate with their soul. 

We at Ayuda NGO are back with an exciting event on the 19th of August marked as World Photography Day. Gen Z assemble, showcase your pictures and fun memories with us through our event 'Life through your lens 2.0'. An opportunity to present your relishing moments in life which we shall cherish together!

Join us by uploading your photos in categories and submit it on the Google form. The best ones from each topics will be picked and will be displayed on our official Instagram Handle. Feel free to join and we will be waiting for you.

08/11/21, 22:34 - +91 95938 82460: Good afternoon sir,/mam
 It‚Äôs really disheartening to see that campus isn‚Äôt opening for the next semester also. Since the cases have been on a constant decline from past 2-3 months as Most of the students are vaccinated and almost all the colleges in the country have reopened, so it's high time that VIT should also consider reopening.

We r almost in our fourth semester but none of us are familiar with the hardware equipment which are used in the respective branches. Online labs and classes can never match the knowledge and thinking we acquire in offline. As a result the learning has been very minimum without any practical implementations.
We are spending a minimum of 8 to 9 hrs. in front of computer screen daily for the classes which has affected our health.

Due to very restricted interaction our soft skills haven‚Äôt been developed yet.

College‚Äôs events and fests like Gravitas and Rivera allows us to learn things beyond our syllabus and gives us one of the best experiences. We are missing that too.
Sitting inside our homes has made life monotonous and dull which has affected our mental well-being.
The online way of pedagogy has been an hindrance to physical, mental, emotional and moral development.
We understand that the campus reopening has been delayed due to our safety issues but considering the declining trend of corona cases and the fact that most of the students have been completely vaccinated we think higher priority should be given to us being able to learn and prosper in the exceptional educational and motivating environment that VIT Vellore has to offer.
We'd be grateful if the campus reopens in the next semester and authorities take actions to do the same.

Sahastra=1000 years
Jojan= 8miles

1 mile= 1.6 km
96000000 x 1.6 = 153600000 km

08/02/22, 18:40 - Karthikeya: Respected Sir,
The following concerns were raised by the students upon receiving the news of physical classes resuming:

1. The college is opening just for a little over 2 months. This will unnecessarily increase the travel expenses, many lost money the first time around when the reopening postponed and with the uncertainty of the cases counts, in case of a surge we will be forced to travel back all during the semester.

2. Since we are being called mid semester, it will be hard to mentally adjust to offline classes for the first time in a short span with classes going on continuously in full swing. The transition will be quite confusing and will hinder the academic performance of the student.

3. International students will have to travel just for 2 months and go back within a short time. Can't book tickets within a short time as it will lead to a viable loss.

4.A lot of us lost close relatives and family during this wave and it will be difficult for us to leave the house. Parents are deeply concerned for our safety due to the same.

5. Many parents are unwilling to send their wards for the current semester and would prefer if they are called for the next after the number of reports stabilizes.

We kindly request you to take these concerns into consideration and do the necessary.

Here are the criteria for Passing the whole¬†COURSE:

In case of¬†Relative Grading¬†:

A candidate

a) Should have secured a¬†minimum of 40% marks in the theory FAT alone.

b) Should have secured a¬†minimum of 50% marks,¬†(¬†out of total marks awarded¬†)¬†to the laboratory and/or project components.

c) Should have secured a minimum of 50% marks, out of the grand total marks awarded to the course (all component marks taken in their credit ratio for 100 marks), for all other course types except the ‚Äòtheory only course‚Äô.

‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.

Let us see a scenario:

Let a subject 'x‚Äô is a 4 credit subject

Theory = 3 credits

J component = 1 credit

Let marks be:

Theory:

25/60 in internals

45/100 in Theory FAT.

( As this guy got 40+ in theory fat alone , he/she's on safe side : condition (a) has met)

Now , Total Theory marks(for 100) = 25 + (45/100)*40 = 25+18 = 43.

[ Even if theory has <50 , this guy can still pass depending on other components. If this course is ‚ÄúTheory-only course", this will be considered as fail. ]

J component:

Let Total marks the guy scored in j comp be : 75/100

( As this guy got 50+ in j component alone , condition (b) has met )

Note: For Lab and J Component, there's no minimum marks criteria in LAB FAT or J Comp Final review. One just need to get 50+ marks out of 100.

‚Ä¶

Now: calculating grand total marks

Grand Total marks= (Theory)*(3/4) + (J Component)*(1/4)

Because total credits are 4, and theory has 3 credits and j comp has 1 credit.

Grand total marks¬†(¬†for 100 )= (43)*(3/4) + (75)*(1/4) =¬†51

As Grand total >=50, this guy has met condition (c) too.

So passed in that course.

Also:

In rare cases, when the course subject is hard / evaluation is strict , ‚ÄúGrand total marks criteria (condition (c))‚Äô‚Äô can go below 50 too. ( But this won't be higher than 50 though )

Grand total marks are ‚Äòceiled'. i.e if grand total marks has a fraction , it is ceiled to next integer. ( Ex: Grand total 49.12 is considered as 50.00)

Hope this helped :)

More info:

>No other¬†marks get ceiled apart from ‚ÄúGrand Total Marks".

>If your course is ‚ÄúTheory-only course", Getting 40 or more out of 100 in FAT and getting 49+ in grand total ( for 100 ) would be enough.

>If one fails in Lab component, whole course need to be re-registered. So be cautious about lab. Be focused while doing all lab assessments so that you can just chill out while attending LAB FAT.

>If one fails to meet only condition- a (i.e failed only in theory), then only theory component need to be re-registered.

Have a good day.

01/08/22, 17:55 - +91 90263 55881: Greetings!

 

We hope you and your family are keeping safe!

 

We have been fighting a long battle against Covid-19. At this crucial moment in humankind, Startups have played a vital role in helping society adapt to new ways. i5 Summit presents a perfect opportunity for entrepreneurs and innovators of startups to showcase their endeavors and gain synergies to excel on their chosen path.

 

i5 Summit is the annual entrepreneurship summit of IIM Indore, held in collaboration with IIT Indore, and is the biggest entrepreneurial meet of central India. It serves as a platform that enables start-ups to get access to funding opportunities and business insights from industry experts through events such as Speaker Series, Panel Discussions, and informal networking events under the Chai Pe Charcha series. The Summit is entering its eighth year in 2021 after a phenomenal edition last year.

 

Our flagship event is the B-Plan competition, GetFunded. The jury thoroughly vets all the startups that apply, and a few selected startups are invited to compete for funding by pitching their ideas. Over the years, several startups operating in a variety of domains have received total funding of INR 140 Million. For this, we thank the investors who have graced our event, among whose number we count such stalwarts as:

 

¬∑ Wadhwani Foundation

¬∑ Matrix Partners 

¬∑ Mumbai Incubator

¬∑ Artha Ventures

 

The i5 Summit has hosted renowned entrepreneurs and CXOs including

¬∑ Mr. Mohandas Pai (Ex-CFO, Infosys)

¬∑ Mr. Venktesh Shukla (Ex-chair, TiE Global) 

¬∑ Mr. Ronnie Screwvala (Founder, UTV) 

 

This year we are thrilled to experience the grandeur of i5 summit‚Äôs speaker series with Prof. Aswath Damodaran. He will be joining the event live from California! He will be enlightening us with the role that finance plays in an entrepreneurial journey.
